abstract: Jessie J., a 23-year-old pop singer, won four MOBO awards, which honor the best music of black origin.
snippet: Jessie J., a 23-year-old pop singer, won four MOBO awards, which honor the best music of black origin.
lead_paragraph: Adele may be the biggest-selling singer and songwriter to come out of Britain in years, but a newcomer to the British pop scene, Jessie J, swept the MOBO awards in Glasgow on Wednesday night, Billboard and other wires services reported. The 23-year-old singer, won best album for her debut effort, "Who You Are," as well as best song for "Do it like a Dude." She also took home awards for best newcomer and best U.K. act.

headline.main: Newcomer Jessie J. Sweeps British Pop Awards
